                                                                                 journals, drawings, etc.) to observe living things.
                                                                              Examples of Learning/Children May:
                                                                              1. Match photographs of different habitats to the things that occupy them
                                                                                 (i.e., worms live in the ground; fish live in water).
                                                                              2. Sequence a series of photographs/pictures of a plant’s growth.
                                                                              3. Sequence a series of photographs/pictures of the life cycle of a butterfly
                                                                                 from caterpillar to chrysalis/cocoon to butterfly.
