                                                                                    eruption. Some events, like an earthquake, happen very quickly; others,
                                                                                    such as the formation of the Grand Canyon, occur very slowly over a time
                                                                                    period much longer than one can observe.
                                                                                 Cross Cutting Concepts:
                                                                                 1. Stability and Change: Things may change rapidly or slowly.
