   only a small fraction of the matter consumed at the lower level is               systems.
   transferred upward, to produce growth and release energy in cellular
   respiration at the higher level. Given this inefficiency, there are generally
   fewer organisms at higher levels of a food web. Some matter reacts to
   release energy for life functions, some matter is stored in newly made
   structures, and much is discarded. The chemical elements that make up the
   molecules of organisms pass through food webs and into and out of the
   atmosphere and soil, and they are combined and recombined in different
   ways. At each link in an ecosystem, matter and energy are conserved.
4. PS3:D Energy in Chemical Processes: The main way that solar energy is
   captured and stored on Earth is through the complex chemical process
   known as photosynthesis.
