SCIENCE
High School, Standard 3. Earth and Space Science
Prepared Graduates:
11. Students can use the full range of science and engineering practices to make sense of natural phenomena and solve problems that
require understanding how human activities and the Earth’s surface processes interact.
Grade Level Expectation:
11. Sustainability of human societies and the biodiversity that supports them requires responsible management of natural resources,
including the development of technologies.
