High School, Standard 3. Earth and Space Science                                                   2020 Colorado Academic Standards          SC.HS.3.12
                                                                                                                                            SC.HS.3.12


Cross Cutting Concepts:
1. Stability and Change: Change and rates of change can be quantified and
   modeled over very short or very long periods of time. Some system changes
   are irreversible.
2. Systems and System Models: When investigating or describing a system, the
   boundaries and initial conditions of the system need to be defined and their
   inputs and outputs analyzed and described using models.
High School, Standard 3. Earth and Space Science                                2020 Colorado Academic Standards SC.HS.3.12
